An iPhone assembled in the US will cost 90% more than the current one, — BOFA. 😳

Imagine your next iPhone costing way more just because of where it's made. Bank of America analysts, led by Wamsi Mohan, dropped a bombshell: if iPhone production moves to the US, labor costs could jack up the price by 25%. 

But wait, it gets wilder—if Apple gets hit with hefty tariffs on imported parts, the total cost could skyrocket by 90% or more. 

Ouch, your wallet might feel that one 🫣
